4965 default:
4966 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected node to lower");
4967 }
4968}
4969
4970// Lower operations with invalid operand or result types (currently used
4971// only for 128-bit integer types).
4972
4973static SDValue lowerI128ToGR128(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue In) {
4974 SDLoc DL(In);
4975 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i64, In,
4976 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, DL));
4977 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, DL, MVT::i64, In,
4978 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(1, DL));
4979 SDNode *Pair = DAG.getMachineNode(SystemZ::PAIR128, DL,
4980 MVT::Untyped, Hi, Lo);
4981 return SDValue(Pair, 0);
4982}
4983
4984static SDValue lowerGR128ToI128(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue In) {
4985 SDLoc DL(In);
4986 SDValue Hi = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(SystemZ::subreg_h64,
4987 DL, MVT::i64, In);
4988 SDValue Lo = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(SystemZ::subreg_l64,
4989 DL, MVT::i64, In);
4990 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_PAIR, DL, MVT::i128, Lo, Hi);
4991}
4992
4993void
4994SystemZTargetLowering::LowerOperationWrapper(SDNode *N,
4995 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
4996 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
4997 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
4998 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: {
4999 SDLoc DL(N);
5000 SDVTList Tys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other);
5001 SDValue Ops[] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1) };
5002 MachineMemOperand *MMO = cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
5003 SDValue Res = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(SystemZISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_128,
5004 DL, Tys, Ops, MVT::i128, MMO);
5005 Results.push_back(lowerGR128ToI128(DAG, Res));
5006 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1));
5007 break;
5008 }
5009 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE: {
5010 SDLoc DL(N);
5011 SDVTList Tys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other);
5012 SDValue Ops[] = { N->getOperand(0),
5013 lowerI128ToGR128(DAG, N->getOperand(2)),
5014 N->getOperand(1) };
5015 MachineMemOperand *MMO = cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
5016 SDValue Res = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(SystemZISD::ATOMIC_STORE_128,
5017 DL, Tys, Ops, MVT::i128, MMO);
5018 // We have to enforce sequential consistency by performing a
5019 // serialization operation after the store.
5020 if (cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getOrdering() ==
5021 AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent)
5022 Res = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(SystemZ::Serialize, DL,
5023 MVT::Other, Res), 0);
5024 Results.push_back(Res);
5025 break;
5026 }
5027 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS: {
5028 SDLoc DL(N);
5029 SDVTList Tys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Untyped, MVT::i32, MVT::Other);
5030 SDValue Ops[] = { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1),
5031 lowerI128ToGR128(DAG, N->getOperand(2)),
5032 lowerI128ToGR128(DAG, N->getOperand(3)) };
5033 MachineMemOperand *MMO = cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
5034 SDValue Res = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(SystemZISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_128,
5035 DL, Tys, Ops, MVT::i128, MMO);
5036 SDValue Success = emitSETCC(DAG, DL, Res.getValue(1),
5037 SystemZ::CCMASK_CS, SystemZ::CCMASK_CS_EQ);
5038 Success = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Success, DL, N->getValueType(1));
5039 Results.push_back(lowerGR128ToI128(DAG, Res));
5040 Results.push_back(Success);
5041 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(2));
5042 break;
5043 }
5044 default:
5045 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected node to lower");
5046 }
5047}
5048
5049void
5050SystemZTargetLowering::ReplaceNodeResults(SDNode *N,
5051 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
5052 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5053 return LowerOperationWrapper(N, Results, DAG);
5054}

5174
5175// Return true if VT is a vector whose elements are a whole number of bytes
5176// in width. Also check for presence of vector support.
5177bool SystemZTargetLowering::canTreatAsByteVector(EVT VT) const {
5178 if (!Subtarget.hasVector())
5179 return false;
5180
5181 return VT.isVector() && VT.getScalarSizeInBits() % 8 == 0 && VT.isSimple();
5182}
5183
5184// Try to simplify an EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT from a vector of type VecVT
5185// producing a result of type ResVT. Op is a possibly bitcast version
5186// of the input vector and Index is the index (based on type VecVT) that
5187// should be extracted. Return the new extraction if a simplification
5188// was possible or if Force is true.
5189SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineExtract(const SDLoc &DL, EVT ResVT,
5190 EVT VecVT, SDValue Op,
5191 unsigned Index,
5192 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
5193 bool Force) const {
5194 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5195
5196 // The number of bytes being extracted.
5197 unsigned BytesPerElement = VecVT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5198
5199 for (;;) {
5200 unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
5201 if (Opcode == ISD::BITCAST)
5202 // Look through bitcasts.
5203 Op = Op.getOperand(0);
5204 else if ((Opcode == ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE || Opcode == SystemZISD::SPLAT) &&
5205 canTreatAsByteVector(Op.getValueType())) {
5206 // Get a VPERM-like permute mask and see whether the bytes covered
5207 // by the extracted element are a contiguous sequence from one
5208 // source operand.
5209 SmallVector<int, SystemZ::VectorBytes> Bytes;
5210 if (!getVPermMask(Op, Bytes))
5211 break;
5212 int First;
5213 if (!getShuffleInput(Bytes, Index * BytesPerElement,
5214 BytesPerElement, First))
5215 break;
5216 if (First < 0)
5217 return DAG.getUNDEF(ResVT);
5218 // Make sure the contiguous sequence starts at a multiple of the
5219 // original element size.
5220 unsigned Byte = unsigned(First) % Bytes.size();
5221 if (Byte % BytesPerElement != 0)
5222 break;
5223 // We can get the extracted value directly from an input.
5224 Index = Byte / BytesPerElement;
5225 Op = Op.getOperand(unsigned(First) / Bytes.size());
5226 Force = true;
5227 } else if (Opcode == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR &&
5228 canTreatAsByteVector(Op.getValueType())) {
5229 // We can only optimize this case if the BUILD_VECTOR elements are
5230 // at least as wide as the extracted value.
5231 EVT OpVT = Op.getValueType();
5232 unsigned OpBytesPerElement = OpVT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5233 if (OpBytesPerElement < BytesPerElement)
5234 break;
5235 // Make sure that the least-significant bit of the extracted value
5236 // is the least significant bit of an input.
5237 unsigned End = (Index + 1) * BytesPerElement;
5238 if (End % OpBytesPerElement != 0)
5239 break;
5240 // We're extracting the low part of one operand of the BUILD_VECTOR.
5241 Op = Op.getOperand(End / OpBytesPerElement - 1);
5242 if (!Op.getValueType().isInteger()) {
5243 EVT VT = MVT::getIntegerVT(Op.getValueSizeInBits());
5244 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Op);
5245 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
5246 }
5247 EVT VT = MVT::getIntegerVT(ResVT.getSizeInBits());
5248 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, VT, Op);
5249 if (VT != ResVT) {
5250 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
5251 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, ResVT, Op);
5252 }
5253 return Op;
5254 } else if ((Opcode == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG ||
5255 Opcode == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG ||
5256 Opcode == ISD::ANY_EXTEND_VECTOR_INREG) &&
5257 canTreatAsByteVector(Op.getValueType()) &&
5258 canTreatAsByteVector(Op.getOperand(0).getValueType())) {
5259 // Make sure that only the unextended bits are significant.
5260 EVT ExtVT = Op.getValueType();
5261 EVT OpVT = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType();
5262 unsigned ExtBytesPerElement = ExtVT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5263 unsigned OpBytesPerElement = OpVT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5264 unsigned Byte = Index * BytesPerElement;
5265 unsigned SubByte = Byte % ExtBytesPerElement;
5266 unsigned MinSubByte = ExtBytesPerElement - OpBytesPerElement;
5267 if (SubByte < MinSubByte ||
5268 SubByte + BytesPerElement > ExtBytesPerElement)
5269 break;
5270 // Get the byte offset of the unextended element
5271 Byte = Byte / ExtBytesPerElement * OpBytesPerElement;
5272 // ...then add the byte offset relative to that element.
5273 Byte += SubByte - MinSubByte;
5274 if (Byte % BytesPerElement != 0)
5275 break;
5276 Op = Op.getOperand(0);
5277 Index = Byte / BytesPerElement;
5278 Force = true;
5279 } else
5280 break;
5281 }
5282 if (Force) {
5283 if (Op.getValueType() != VecVT) {
5284 Op = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VecVT, Op);
5285 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
5286 }
5287 return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, ResVT, Op,
5288 DAG.getConstant(Index, DL, MVT::i32));
5289 }
5290 return SDValue();
5291}
5292
5293// Optimize vector operations in scalar value Op on the basis that Op
5294// is truncated to TruncVT.
5295SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineTruncateExtract(
5296 const SDLoc &DL, EVT TruncVT, SDValue Op, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5297 // If we have (trunc (extract_vector_elt X, Y)), try to turn it into
5298 // (extract_vector_elt (bitcast X), Y'), where (bitcast X) has elements
5299 // of type TruncVT.
5300 if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5301 TruncVT.getSizeInBits() % 8 == 0) {
5302 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5303 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
5304 if (canTreatAsByteVector(VecVT)) {
5305 if (auto *IndexN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))) {
5306 unsigned BytesPerElement = VecVT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5307 unsigned TruncBytes = TruncVT.getStoreSize();
5308 if (BytesPerElement % TruncBytes == 0) {
5309 // Calculate the value of Y' in the above description. We are
5310 // splitting the original elements into Scale equal-sized pieces
5311 // and for truncation purposes want the last (least-significant)
5312 // of these pieces for IndexN. This is easiest to do by calculating
5313 // the start index of the following element and then subtracting 1.
5314 unsigned Scale = BytesPerElement / TruncBytes;
5315 unsigned NewIndex = (IndexN->getZExtValue() + 1) * Scale - 1;
5316
5317 // Defer the creation of the bitcast from X to combineExtract,
5318 // which might be able to optimize the extraction.
5319 VecVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(TruncBytes * 8),
5320 VecVT.getStoreSize() / TruncBytes);
5321 EVT ResVT = (TruncBytes < 4 ? MVT::i32 : TruncVT);
5322 return combineExtract(DL, ResVT, VecVT, Vec, NewIndex, DCI, true);
5323 }
5324 }
5325 }
5326 }
5327 return SDValue();
5328}
5329
5330SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineZERO_EXTEND(
5331 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5332 // Convert (zext (select_ccmask C1, C2)) into (select_ccmask C1', C2')
5333 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5334 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
5335 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5336 if (N0.getOpcode() == SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK) {
5337 auto *TrueOp = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(0));
5338 auto *FalseOp = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1));
5339 if (TrueOp && FalseOp) {
5340 SDLoc DL(N0);
5341 SDValue Ops[] = { DAG.getConstant(TrueOp->getZExtValue(), DL, VT),
5342 DAG.getConstant(FalseOp->getZExtValue(), DL, VT),
5343 N0.getOperand(2), N0.getOperand(3), N0.getOperand(4) };
5344 SDValue NewSelect = DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK, DL, VT, Ops);
5345 // If N0 has multiple uses, change other uses as well.
5346 if (!N0.hasOneUse()) {
5347 SDValue TruncSelect =
5348 DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, N0.getValueType(), NewSelect);
5349 DCI.CombineTo(N0.getNode(), TruncSelect);
5350 }
5351 return NewSelect;
5352 }
5353 }
5354 return SDValue();
5355}
5356
5357SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineSIGN_EXTEND_INREG(
5358 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5359 // Convert (sext_in_reg (setcc LHS, RHS, COND), i1)
5360 // and (sext_in_reg (any_extend (setcc LHS, RHS, COND)), i1)
5361 // into (select_cc LHS, RHS, -1, 0, COND)
5362 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5363 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
5364 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5365 EVT EVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT();
5366 if (N0.hasOneUse() && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
5367 N0 = N0.getOperand(0);
5368 if (EVT == MVT::i1 && N0.hasOneUse() && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
5369 SDLoc DL(N0);
5370 SDValue Ops[] = { N0.getOperand(0), N0.getOperand(1),
5371 DAG.getConstant(-1, DL, VT), DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT),
5372 N0.getOperand(2) };
5373 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, DL, VT, Ops);
5374 }
5375 return SDValue();
5376}
5377
5378SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineSIGN_EXTEND(
5379 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5380 // Convert (sext (ashr (shl X, C1), C2)) to
5381 // (ashr (shl (anyext X), C1'), C2')), since wider shifts are as
5382 // cheap as narrower ones.
5383 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5384 SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
5385 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5386 if (N0.hasOneUse() && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) {
5387 auto *SraAmt = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1));
5388 SDValue Inner = N0.getOperand(0);
5389 if (SraAmt && Inner.hasOneUse() && Inner.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
5390 if (auto *ShlAmt = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Inner.getOperand(1))) {
5391 unsigned Extra = (VT.getSizeInBits() - N0.getValueSizeInBits());
5392 unsigned NewShlAmt = ShlAmt->getZExtValue() + Extra;
5393 unsigned NewSraAmt = SraAmt->getZExtValue() + Extra;
5394 EVT ShiftVT = N0.getOperand(1).getValueType();
5395 SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(Inner), VT,
5396 Inner.getOperand(0));
5397 SDValue Shl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SDLoc(Inner), VT, Ext,
5398 DAG.getConstant(NewShlAmt, SDLoc(Inner),
5399 ShiftVT));
5400 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, SDLoc(N0), VT, Shl,
5401 DAG.getConstant(NewSraAmt, SDLoc(N0), ShiftVT));
5402 }
5403 }
5404 }
5405 return SDValue();
5406}
5407
5408SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineMERGE(
5409 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5410 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5411 unsigned Opcode = N->getOpcode();
5412 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
5413 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
5414 if (Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
5415 Op0 = Op0.getOperand(0);
5416 if (ISD::isBuildVectorAllZeros(Op0.getNode())) {
5417 // (z_merge_* 0, 0) -> 0. This is mostly useful for using VLLEZF
5418 // for v4f32.
5419 if (Op1 == N->getOperand(0))
5420 return Op1;
5421 // (z_merge_? 0, X) -> (z_unpackl_? 0, X).
5422 EVT VT = Op1.getValueType();
5423 unsigned ElemBytes = VT.getVectorElementType().getStoreSize();
5424 if (ElemBytes <= 4) {
5425 Opcode = (Opcode == SystemZISD::MERGE_HIGH ?
5426 SystemZISD::UNPACKL_HIGH : SystemZISD::UNPACKL_LOW);
5427 EVT InVT = VT.changeVectorElementTypeToInteger();
5428 EVT OutVT = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(ElemBytes * 16),
5429 SystemZ::VectorBytes / ElemBytes / 2);
5430 if (VT != InVT) {
5431 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N), InVT, Op1);
5432 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op1.getNode());
5433 }
5434 SDValue Op = DAG.getNode(Opcode, SDLoc(N), OutVT, Op1);
5435 DCI.AddToWorklist(Op.getNode());
5436 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(N), VT, Op);
5437 }
5438 }
5439 return SDValue();
5440}
5441
5442SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineLOAD(
5443 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5444 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5445 EVT LdVT = N->getValueType(0);
5446 if (LdVT.isVector() || LdVT.isInteger())
5447 return SDValue();
5448 // Transform a scalar load that is REPLICATEd as well as having other
5449 // use(s) to the form where the other use(s) use the first element of the
5450 // REPLICATE instead of the load. Otherwise instruction selection will not
5451 // produce a VLREP. Avoid extracting to a GPR, so only do this for floating
5452 // point loads.
5453
5454 SDValue Replicate;
5455 SmallVector<SDNode*, 8> OtherUses;
5456 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = N->use_begin(), UE = N->use_end();
5457 UI != UE; ++UI) {
5458 if (UI->getOpcode() == SystemZISD::REPLICATE) {
5459 if (Replicate)
5460 return SDValue(); // Should never happen
5461 Replicate = SDValue(*UI, 0);
5462 }
5463 else if (UI.getUse().getResNo() == 0)
5464 OtherUses.push_back(*UI);
5465 }
5466 if (!Replicate || OtherUses.empty())
5467 return SDValue();
5468
5469 SDLoc DL(N);
5470 SDValue Extract0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, LdVT,
5471 Replicate, DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
5472 // Update uses of the loaded Value while preserving old chains.
5473 for (SDNode *U : OtherUses) {
5474 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
5475 for (SDValue Op : U->ops())
5476 Ops.push_back((Op.getNode() == N && Op.getResNo() == 0) ? Extract0 : Op);
5477 DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(U, Ops);
5478 }
5479 return SDValue(N, 0);
5480}
5481
5482SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineSTORE(
5483 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5484 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5485 auto *SN = cast<StoreSDNode>(N);
5486 auto &Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
5487 EVT MemVT = SN->getMemoryVT();
5488 // If we have (truncstoreiN (extract_vector_elt X, Y), Z) then it is better
5489 // for the extraction to be done on a vMiN value, so that we can use VSTE.
5490 // If X has wider elements then convert it to:
5491 // (truncstoreiN (extract_vector_elt (bitcast X), Y2), Z).
5492 if (MemVT.isInteger() && SN->isTruncatingStore()) {
5493 if (SDValue Value =
5494 combineTruncateExtract(SDLoc(N), MemVT, SN->getValue(), DCI)) {
5495 DCI.AddToWorklist(Value.getNode());
5496
5497 // Rewrite the store with the new form of stored value.
5498 return DAG.getTruncStore(SN->getChain(), SDLoc(SN), Value,
5499 SN->getBasePtr(), SN->getMemoryVT(),
5500 SN->getMemOperand());
5501 }
5502 }
5503 // Combine STORE (BSWAP) into STRVH/STRV/STRVG
5504 if (!SN->isTruncatingStore() &&
5505 Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::BSWAP &&
5506 Op1.getNode()->hasOneUse() &&
5507 (Op1.getValueType() == MVT::i16 ||
5508 Op1.getValueType() == MVT::i32 ||
5509 Op1.getValueType() == MVT::i64)) {
5510
5511 SDValue BSwapOp = Op1.getOperand(0);
5512
5513 if (BSwapOp.getValueType() == MVT::i16)
5514 BSwapOp = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32, BSwapOp);
5515
5516 SDValue Ops[] = {
5517 N->getOperand(0), BSwapOp, N->getOperand(2)
5518 };
5519
5520 return
5521 DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(SystemZISD::STRV, SDLoc(N), DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other),
5522 Ops, MemVT, SN->getMemOperand());
5523 }
5524 return SDValue();
5525}
5526
5527SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(
5528 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5529
5530 if (!Subtarget.hasVector())
5531 return SDValue();
5532
5533 // Try to simplify a vector extraction.
5534 if (auto *IndexN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))) {
5535 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
5536 EVT VecVT = Op0.getValueType();
5537 return combineExtract(SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), VecVT, Op0,
5538 IndexN->getZExtValue(), DCI, false);
5539 }
5540 return SDValue();
5541}
5542
5543SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineJOIN_DWORDS(
5544 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5545 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5546 // (join_dwords X, X) == (replicate X)
5547 if (N->getOperand(0) == N->getOperand(1))
5548 return DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::REPLICATE, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
5549 N->getOperand(0));
5550 return SDValue();
5551}
5552
5553SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineFP_ROUND(
5554 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5555
5556 if (!Subtarget.hasVector())
5557 return SDValue();
5558
5559 // (fpround (extract_vector_elt X 0))
5560 // (fpround (extract_vector_elt X 1)) ->
5561 // (extract_vector_elt (VROUND X) 0)
5562 // (extract_vector_elt (VROUND X) 2)
5563 //
5564 // This is a special case since the target doesn't really support v2f32s.
5565 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5566 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
5567 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::f32 &&
5568 Op0.hasOneUse() &&
5569 Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5570 Op0.getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::v2f64 &&
5571 Op0.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant &&
5572 cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() == 0) {
5573 SDValue Vec = Op0.getOperand(0);
5574 for (auto *U : Vec->uses()) {
5575 if (U != Op0.getNode() &&
5576 U->hasOneUse() &&
5577 U->getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5578 U->getOperand(0) == Vec &&
5579 U->getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant &&
5580 cast<ConstantSDNode>(U->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() == 1) {
5581 SDValue OtherRound = SDValue(*U->use_begin(), 0);
5582 if (OtherRound.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_ROUND &&
5583 OtherRound.getOperand(0) == SDValue(U, 0) &&
5584 OtherRound.getValueType() == MVT::f32) {
5585 SDValue VRound = DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::VROUND, SDLoc(N),
5586 MVT::v4f32, Vec);
5587 DCI.AddToWorklist(VRound.getNode());
5588 SDValue Extract1 =
5589 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(U), MVT::f32,
5590 VRound, DAG.getConstant(2, SDLoc(U), MVT::i32));
5591 DCI.AddToWorklist(Extract1.getNode());
5592 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(OtherRound, Extract1);
5593 SDValue Extract0 =
5594 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(Op0), MVT::f32,
5595 VRound, DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(Op0), MVT::i32));
5596 return Extract0;
5597 }
5598 }
5599 }
5600 }
5601 return SDValue();
5602}
5603
5604SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineFP_EXTEND(
5605 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5606
5607 if (!Subtarget.hasVector())
5608 return SDValue();
5609
5610 // (fpextend (extract_vector_elt X 0))
5611 // (fpextend (extract_vector_elt X 2)) ->
5612 // (extract_vector_elt (VEXTEND X) 0)
5613 // (extract_vector_elt (VEXTEND X) 1)
5614 //
5615 // This is a special case since the target doesn't really support v2f32s.
5616 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5617 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
5618 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::f64 &&
5619 Op0.hasOneUse() &&
5620 Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5621 Op0.getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::v4f32 &&
5622 Op0.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant &&
5623 cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() == 0) {
5624 SDValue Vec = Op0.getOperand(0);
5625 for (auto *U : Vec->uses()) {
5626 if (U != Op0.getNode() &&
5627 U->hasOneUse() &&
5628 U->getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT &&
5629 U->getOperand(0) == Vec &&
5630 U->getOperand(1).getOpcode() == ISD::Constant &&
5631 cast<ConstantSDNode>(U->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() == 2) {
5632 SDValue OtherExtend = SDValue(*U->use_begin(), 0);
5633 if (OtherExtend.getOpcode() == ISD::FP_EXTEND &&
5634 OtherExtend.getOperand(0) == SDValue(U, 0) &&
5635 OtherExtend.getValueType() == MVT::f64) {
5636 SDValue VExtend = DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::VEXTEND, SDLoc(N),
5637 MVT::v2f64, Vec);
5638 DCI.AddToWorklist(VExtend.getNode());
5639 SDValue Extract1 =
5640 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(U), MVT::f64,
5641 VExtend, DAG.getConstant(1, SDLoc(U), MVT::i32));
5642 DCI.AddToWorklist(Extract1.getNode());
5643 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(OtherExtend, Extract1);
5644 SDValue Extract0 =
5645 DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SDLoc(Op0), MVT::f64,
5646 VExtend, DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(Op0), MVT::i32));
5647 return Extract0;
5648 }
5649 }
5650 }
5651 }
5652 return SDValue();
5653}
5654
5655SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineBSWAP(
5656 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5657 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5658 // Combine BSWAP (LOAD) into LRVH/LRV/LRVG
5659 if (ISD::isNON_EXTLoad(N->getOperand(0).getNode()) &&
5660 N->getOperand(0).hasOneUse() &&
5661 (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i16 || N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 ||
5662 N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i64)) {
5663 SDValue Load = N->getOperand(0);
5664 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Load);
5665
5666 // Create the byte-swapping load.
5667 SDValue Ops[] = {
5668 LD->getChain(), // Chain
5669 LD->getBasePtr() // Ptr
5670 };
5671 EVT LoadVT = N->getValueType(0);
5672 if (LoadVT == MVT::i16)
5673 LoadVT = MVT::i32;
5674 SDValue BSLoad =
5675 DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(SystemZISD::LRV, SDLoc(N),
5676 DAG.getVTList(LoadVT, MVT::Other),
5677 Ops, LD->getMemoryVT(), LD->getMemOperand());
5678
5679 // If this is an i16 load, insert the truncate.
5680 SDValue ResVal = BSLoad;
5681 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i16)
5682 ResVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SDLoc(N), MVT::i16, BSLoad);
5683
5684 // First, combine the bswap away. This makes the value produced by the
5685 // load dead.
5686 DCI.CombineTo(N, ResVal);
5687
5688 // Next, combine the load away, we give it a bogus result value but a real
5689 // chain result. The result value is dead because the bswap is dead.
5690 DCI.CombineTo(Load.getNode(), ResVal, BSLoad.getValue(1));
5691
5692 // Return N so it doesn't get rechecked!
5693 return SDValue(N, 0);
5694 }
5695 return SDValue();
5696}
5697
5698static bool combineCCMask(SDValue &CCReg, int &CCValid, int &CCMask) {
5699 // We have a SELECT_CCMASK or BR_CCMASK comparing the condition code
5700 // set by the CCReg instruction using the CCValid / CCMask masks,
5701 // If the CCReg instruction is itself a ICMP testing the condition
5702 // code set by some other instruction, see whether we can directly
5703 // use that condition code.
5704
5705 // Verify that we have an ICMP against some constant.
5706 if (CCValid != SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP)
5707 return false;
5708 auto *ICmp = CCReg.getNode();
5709 if (ICmp->getOpcode() != SystemZISD::ICMP)
5710 return false;
5711 auto *CompareLHS = ICmp->getOperand(0).getNode();
5712 auto *CompareRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(ICmp->getOperand(1));
5713 if (!CompareRHS)
5714 return false;
5715
5716 // Optimize the case where CompareLHS is a SELECT_CCMASK.
5717 if (CompareLHS->getOpcode() == SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK) {
5718 // Verify that we have an appropriate mask for a EQ or NE comparison.
5719 bool Invert = false;
5720 if (CCMask == SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
5721 Invert = !Invert;
5722 else if (CCMask != SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_EQ)
5723 return false;
5724
5725 // Verify that the ICMP compares against one of select values.
5726 auto *TrueVal = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CompareLHS->getOperand(0));
5727 if (!TrueVal)
5728 return false;
5729 auto *FalseVal = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CompareLHS->getOperand(1));
5730 if (!FalseVal)
5731 return false;
5732 if (CompareRHS->getZExtValue() == FalseVal->getZExtValue())
5733 Invert = !Invert;
5734 else if (CompareRHS->getZExtValue() != TrueVal->getZExtValue())
5735 return false;
5736
5737 // Compute the effective CC mask for the new branch or select.
5738 auto *NewCCValid = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CompareLHS->getOperand(2));
5739 auto *NewCCMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CompareLHS->getOperand(3));
5740 if (!NewCCValid || !NewCCMask)
5741 return false;
5742 CCValid = NewCCValid->getZExtValue();
5743 CCMask = NewCCMask->getZExtValue();
5744 if (Invert)
5745 CCMask ^= CCValid;
5746
5747 // Return the updated CCReg link.
5748 CCReg = CompareLHS->getOperand(4);
5749 return true;
5750 }
5751
5752 // Optimize the case where CompareRHS is (SRA (SHL (IPM))).
5753 if (CompareLHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA) {
5754 auto *SRACount = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CompareLHS->getOperand(1));
5755 if (!SRACount || SRACount->getZExtValue() != 30)
5756 return false;
5757 auto *SHL = CompareLHS->getOperand(0).getNode();
5758 if (SHL->getOpcode() != ISD::SHL)
5759 return false;
5760 auto *SHLCount = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(SHL->getOperand(1));
5761 if (!SHLCount || SHLCount->getZExtValue() != 30 - SystemZ::IPM_CC)
5762 return false;
5763 auto *IPM = SHL->getOperand(0).getNode();
5764 if (IPM->getOpcode() != SystemZISD::IPM)
5765 return false;
5766
5767 // Avoid introducing CC spills (because SRA would clobber CC).
5768 if (!CompareLHS->hasOneUse())
5769 return false;
5770 // Verify that the ICMP compares against zero.
5771 if (CompareRHS->getZExtValue() != 0)
5772 return false;
5773
5774 // Compute the effective CC mask for the new branch or select.
5775 switch (CCMask) {
5776 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_EQ: break;
5777 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE: break;
5778 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_LT: CCMask = SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_GT; break;
5779 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_GT: CCMask = SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_LT; break;
5780 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_LE: CCMask = SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_GE; break;
5781 case SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_GE: CCMask = SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_LE; break;
5782 default: return false;
5783 }
5784
5785 // Return the updated CCReg link.
5786 CCReg = IPM->getOperand(0);
5787 return true;
5788 }
5789
5790 return false;
5791}
5792
5793SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineBR_CCMASK(
5794 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5795 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5796
5797 // Combine BR_CCMASK (ICMP (SELECT_CCMASK)) into a single BR_CCMASK.
5798 auto *CCValid = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
5799 auto *CCMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2));
5800 if (!CCValid || !CCMask)
5801 return SDValue();
5802
5803 int CCValidVal = CCValid->getZExtValue();
5804 int CCMaskVal = CCMask->getZExtValue();
5805 SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
5806 SDValue CCReg = N->getOperand(4);
5807
5808 if (combineCCMask(CCReg, CCValidVal, CCMaskVal))
5809 return DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::BR_CCMASK, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
5810 Chain,
5811 DAG.getConstant(CCValidVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32),
5812 DAG.getConstant(CCMaskVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32),
5813 N->getOperand(3), CCReg);
5814 return SDValue();
5815}
5816
5817SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineSELECT_CCMASK(
5818 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5819 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5820
5821 // Combine SELECT_CCMASK (ICMP (SELECT_CCMASK)) into a single SELECT_CCMASK.
5822 auto *CCValid = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2));
5823 auto *CCMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(3));
5824 if (!CCValid || !CCMask)
5825 return SDValue();
5826
5827 int CCValidVal = CCValid->getZExtValue();
5828 int CCMaskVal = CCMask->getZExtValue();
5829 SDValue CCReg = N->getOperand(4);
5830
5831 if (combineCCMask(CCReg, CCValidVal, CCMaskVal))
5832 return DAG.getNode(SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0),
5833 N->getOperand(0),
5834 N->getOperand(1),
5835 DAG.getConstant(CCValidVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32),
5836 DAG.getConstant(CCMaskVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32),
5837 CCReg);
5838 return SDValue();
5839}
5840
5841
5842SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineGET_CCMASK(
5843 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5844
5845 // Optimize away GET_CCMASK (SELECT_CCMASK) if the CC masks are compatible
5846 auto *CCValid = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
5847 auto *CCMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2));
5848 if (!CCValid || !CCMask)
5849 return SDValue();
5850 int CCValidVal = CCValid->getZExtValue();
5851 int CCMaskVal = CCMask->getZExtValue();
5852
5853 SDValue Select = N->getOperand(0);
5854 if (Select->getOpcode() != SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK)
5855 return SDValue();
5856
5857 auto *SelectCCValid = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Select->getOperand(2));
5858 auto *SelectCCMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Select->getOperand(3));
5859 if (!SelectCCValid || !SelectCCMask)
5860 return SDValue();
5861 int SelectCCValidVal = SelectCCValid->getZExtValue();
5862 int SelectCCMaskVal = SelectCCMask->getZExtValue();
5863
5864 auto *TrueVal = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Select->getOperand(0));
5865 auto *FalseVal = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Select->getOperand(1));
5866 if (!TrueVal || !FalseVal)
5867 return SDValue();
5868 if (TrueVal->getZExtValue() != 0 && FalseVal->getZExtValue() == 0)
5869 ;
5870 else if (TrueVal->getZExtValue() == 0 && FalseVal->getZExtValue() != 0)
5871 SelectCCMaskVal ^= SelectCCValidVal;
5872 else
5873 return SDValue();
5874
5875 if (SelectCCValidVal & ~CCValidVal)
5876 return SDValue();
5877 if (SelectCCMaskVal != (CCMaskVal & SelectCCValidVal))
5878 return SDValue();
5879
5880 return Select->getOperand(4);
5881}
5882
5883SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::combineIntDIVREM(
5884 SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5885 SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
5886 EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
5887 // In the case where the divisor is a vector of constants a cheaper
5888 // sequence of instructions can replace the divide. BuildSDIV is called to
5889 // do this during DAG combining, but it only succeeds when it can build a
5890 // multiplication node. The only option for SystemZ is ISD::SMUL_LOHI, and
5891 // since it is not Legal but Custom it can only happen before
5892 // legalization. Therefore we must scalarize this early before Combine
5893 // 1. For widened vectors, this is already the result of type legalization.
5894 if (DCI.Level == BeforeLegalizeTypes && VT.isVector() && isTypeLegal(VT) &&
5895 DAG.isConstantIntBuildVectorOrConstantInt(N->getOperand(1)))
5896 return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(N);
5897 return SDValue();
5898}
5899
5900SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::unwrapAddress(SDValue N) const {
5901 if (N->getOpcode() == SystemZISD::PCREL_WRAPPER)
5902 return N->getOperand(0);
5903 return N;
5904}
5905
5906SDValue SystemZTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
5907 DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
5908 switch(N->getOpcode()) {
5909 default: break;
5910 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: return combineZERO_EXTEND(N, DCI);
5911 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: return combineSIGN_EXTEND(N, DCI);
5912 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: return combineSIGN_EXTEND_INREG(N, DCI);
5913 case SystemZISD::MERGE_HIGH:
5914 case SystemZISD::MERGE_LOW: return combineMERGE(N, DCI);
5915 case ISD::LOAD: return combineLOAD(N, DCI);
5916 case ISD::STORE: return combineSTORE(N, DCI);
5917 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: return combineEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(N, DCI);
5918 case SystemZISD::JOIN_DWORDS: return combineJOIN_DWORDS(N, DCI);
5919 case ISD::FP_ROUND: return combineFP_ROUND(N, DCI);
5920 case ISD::FP_EXTEND: return combineFP_EXTEND(N, DCI);
5921 case ISD::BSWAP: return combineBSWAP(N, DCI);
5922 case SystemZISD::BR_CCMASK: return combineBR_CCMASK(N, DCI);
5923 case SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK: return combineSELECT_CCMASK(N, DCI);
5924 case SystemZISD::GET_CCMASK: return combineGET_CCMASK(N, DCI);
5925 case ISD::SDIV:
5926 case ISD::UDIV:
5927 case ISD::SREM:
5928 case ISD::UREM: return combineIntDIVREM(N, DCI);
5929 }
5930
5931 return SDValue();
5932}
5933
5934// Return the demanded elements for the OpNo source operand of Op. DemandedElts
5935// are for Op.
5936static APInt getDemandedSrcElements(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts,
5937 unsigned OpNo) {
5938 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
5939 unsigned NumElts = (VT.isVector() ? VT.getVectorNumElements() : 1);
5940 APInt SrcDemE;
5941 unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
5942 if (Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN) {
5943 unsigned Id = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
5944 switch (Id) {
5945 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksh: // PACKS
5946 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksf:
5947 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksg:
5948 case Intrinsic::s390_vpkshs: // PACKS_CC
5949 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksfs:
5950 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksgs:
5951 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsh: // PACKLS
5952 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsf:
5953 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsg:
5954 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklshs: // PACKLS_CC
5955 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsfs:
5956 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsgs:
5957 // VECTOR PACK truncates the elements of two source vectors into one.
5958 SrcDemE = DemandedElts;
5959 if (OpNo == 2)
5960 SrcDemE.lshrInPlace(NumElts / 2);
5961 SrcDemE = SrcDemE.trunc(NumElts / 2);
5962 break;
5963 // VECTOR UNPACK extends half the elements of the source vector.
5964 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphb: // VECTOR UNPACK HIGH
5965 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphh:
5966 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphf:
5967 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOGICAL HIGH
5968 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhh:
5969 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhf:
5970 SrcDemE = APInt(NumElts * 2, 0);
5971 SrcDemE.insertBits(DemandedElts, 0);
5972 break;
5973 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOW
5974 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhw:
5975 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplf:
5976 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOGICAL LOW
5977 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllh:
5978 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllf:
5979 SrcDemE = APInt(NumElts * 2, 0);
5980 SrcDemE.insertBits(DemandedElts, NumElts);
5981 break;
5982 case Intrinsic::s390_vpdi: {
5983 // VECTOR PERMUTE DWORD IMMEDIATE selects one element from each source.
5984 SrcDemE = APInt(NumElts, 0);
5985 if (!DemandedElts[OpNo - 1])
5986 break;
5987 unsigned Mask = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
5988 unsigned MaskBit = ((OpNo - 1) ? 1 : 4);
5989 // Demand input element 0 or 1, given by the mask bit value.
5990 SrcDemE.setBit((Mask & MaskBit)? 1 : 0);
5991 break;
5992 }
5993 case Intrinsic::s390_vsldb: {
5994 // VECTOR SHIFT LEFT DOUBLE BY BYTE
5995 assert(VT == MVT::v16i8 && "Unexpected type.");
5996 unsigned FirstIdx = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
5997 assert (FirstIdx > 0 && FirstIdx < 16 && "Unused operand.");
5998 unsigned NumSrc0Els = 16 - FirstIdx;
5999 SrcDemE = APInt(NumElts, 0);
6000 if (OpNo == 1) {
6001 APInt DemEls = DemandedElts.trunc(NumSrc0Els);
6002 SrcDemE.insertBits(DemEls, FirstIdx);
6003 } else {
6004 APInt DemEls = DemandedElts.lshr(NumSrc0Els);
6005 SrcDemE.insertBits(DemEls, 0);
6006 }
6007 break;
6008 }
6009 case Intrinsic::s390_vperm:
6010 SrcDemE = APInt(NumElts, 1);
6011 break;
6012 default:
6013 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled intrinsic.");
6014 break;
6015 }
6016 } else {
6017 switch (Opcode) {
6018 case SystemZISD::JOIN_DWORDS:
6019 // Scalar operand.
6020 SrcDemE = APInt(1, 1);
6021 break;
6022 case SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK:
6023 SrcDemE = DemandedElts;
6024 break;
6025 default:
6026 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled opcode.");
6027 break;
6028 }
6029 }
6030 return SrcDemE;
6031}
6032
6033static void computeKnownBitsBinOp(const SDValue Op, KnownBits &Known,
6034 const APInt &DemandedElts,
6035 const SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Depth,
6036 unsigned OpNo) {
6037 APInt Src0DemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, OpNo);
6038 APInt Src1DemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, OpNo + 1);
6039 KnownBits LHSKnown =
6040 DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(OpNo), Src0DemE, Depth + 1);
6041 KnownBits RHSKnown =
6042 DAG.computeKnownBits(Op.getOperand(OpNo + 1), Src1DemE, Depth + 1);
6043 Known.Zero = LHSKnown.Zero & RHSKnown.Zero;
6044 Known.One = LHSKnown.One & RHSKnown.One;
6045}
6046
6047void
6048SystemZTargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetNode(const SDValue Op,
6049 KnownBits &Known,
6050 const APInt &DemandedElts,
6051 const SelectionDAG &DAG,
6052 unsigned Depth) const {
6053 Known.resetAll();
6054
6055 // Intrinsic CC result is returned in the two low bits.
6056 unsigned tmp0, tmp1; // not used
6057 if (Op.getResNo() == 1 && isIntrinsicWithCC(Op, tmp0, tmp1)) {
6058 Known.Zero.setBitsFrom(2);
6059 return;
6060 }
6061 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
6062 if (Op.getResNo() != 0 || VT == MVT::Untyped)
6063 return;
6064 assert (Known.getBitWidth() == VT.getScalarSizeInBits() &&
6065 "KnownBits does not match VT in bitwidth");
6066 assert ((!VT.isVector() ||
6067 (DemandedElts.getBitWidth() == VT.getVectorNumElements())) &&
6068 "DemandedElts does not match VT number of elements");
6069 unsigned BitWidth = Known.getBitWidth();
6070 unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
6071 if (Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN) {
6072 bool IsLogical = false;
6073 unsigned Id = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
6074 switch (Id) {
6075 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksh: // PACKS
6076 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksf:
6077 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksg:
6078 case Intrinsic::s390_vpkshs: // PACKS_CC
6079 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksfs:
6080 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksgs:
6081 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsh: // PACKLS
6082 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsf:
6083 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsg:
6084 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklshs: // PACKLS_CC
6085 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsfs:
6086 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsgs:
6087 case Intrinsic::s390_vpdi:
6088 case Intrinsic::s390_vsldb:
6089 case Intrinsic::s390_vperm:
6090 computeKnownBitsBinOp(Op, Known, DemandedElts, DAG, Depth, 1);
6091 break;
6092 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOGICAL HIGH
6093 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhh:
6094 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhf:
6095 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOGICAL LOW
6096 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllh:
6097 case Intrinsic::s390_vupllf:
6098 IsLogical = true;
6099 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
6100 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphb: // VECTOR UNPACK HIGH
6101 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphh:
6102 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphf:
6103 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOW
6104 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhw:
6105 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplf: {
6106 SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(1);
6107 APInt SrcDemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, 0);
6108 Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(SrcOp, SrcDemE, Depth + 1);
6109 if (IsLogical) {
6110 Known = Known.zext(BitWidth, true);
6111 } else
6112 Known = Known.sext(BitWidth);
6113 break;
6114 }
6115 default:
6116 break;
6117 }
6118 } else {
6119 switch (Opcode) {
6120 case SystemZISD::JOIN_DWORDS:
6121 case SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK:
6122 computeKnownBitsBinOp(Op, Known, DemandedElts, DAG, Depth, 0);
6123 break;
6124 case SystemZISD::REPLICATE: {
6125 SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(0);
6126 Known = DAG.computeKnownBits(SrcOp, Depth + 1);
6127 if (Known.getBitWidth() < BitWidth && isa<ConstantSDNode>(SrcOp))
6128 Known = Known.sext(BitWidth); // VREPI sign extends the immedate.
6129 break;
6130 }
6131 default:
6132 break;
6133 }
6134 }
6135
6136 // Known has the width of the source operand(s). Adjust if needed to match
6137 // the passed bitwidth.
6138 if (Known.getBitWidth() != BitWidth)
6139 Known = Known.zextOrTrunc(BitWidth, false);
6140}
6141
6142static unsigned computeNumSignBitsBinOp(SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts,
6143 const SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Depth,
6144 unsigned OpNo) {
6145 APInt Src0DemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, OpNo);
6146 unsigned LHS = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(OpNo), Src0DemE, Depth + 1);
6147 if (LHS == 1) return 1; // Early out.
6148 APInt Src1DemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, OpNo + 1);
6149 unsigned RHS = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(Op.getOperand(OpNo + 1), Src1DemE, Depth + 1);
6150 if (RHS == 1) return 1; // Early out.
6151 unsigned Common = std::min(LHS, RHS);
6152 unsigned SrcBitWidth = Op.getOperand(OpNo).getScalarValueSizeInBits();
6153 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
6154 unsigned VTBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
6155 if (SrcBitWidth > VTBits) { // PACK
6156 unsigned SrcExtraBits = SrcBitWidth - VTBits;
6157 if (Common > SrcExtraBits)
6158 return (Common - SrcExtraBits);
6159 return 1;
6160 }
6161 assert (SrcBitWidth == VTBits && "Expected operands of same bitwidth.");
6162 return Common;
6163}
6164
6165unsigned
6166SystemZTargetLowering::ComputeNumSignBitsForTargetNode(
6167 SDValue Op, const APInt &DemandedElts, const SelectionDAG &DAG,
6168 unsigned Depth) const {
6169 if (Op.getResNo() != 0)
6170 return 1;
6171 unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
6172 if (Opcode == ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN) {
6173 unsigned Id = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
6174 switch (Id) {
6175 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksh: // PACKS
6176 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksf:
6177 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksg:
6178 case Intrinsic::s390_vpkshs: // PACKS_CC
6179 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksfs:
6180 case Intrinsic::s390_vpksgs:
6181 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsh: // PACKLS
6182 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsf:
6183 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsg:
6184 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklshs: // PACKLS_CC
6185 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsfs:
6186 case Intrinsic::s390_vpklsgs:
6187 case Intrinsic::s390_vpdi:
6188 case Intrinsic::s390_vsldb:
6189 case Intrinsic::s390_vperm:
6190 return computeNumSignBitsBinOp(Op, DemandedElts, DAG, Depth, 1);
6191 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphb: // VECTOR UNPACK HIGH
6192 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphh:
6193 case Intrinsic::s390_vuphf:
6194 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplb: // VECTOR UNPACK LOW
6195 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplhw:
6196 case Intrinsic::s390_vuplf: {
6197 SDValue PackedOp = Op.getOperand(1);
6198 APInt SrcDemE = getDemandedSrcElements(Op, DemandedElts, 1);
6199 unsigned Tmp = DAG.ComputeNumSignBits(PackedOp, SrcDemE, Depth + 1);
6200 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
6201 unsigned VTBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
6202 Tmp += VTBits - PackedOp.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
6203 return Tmp;
6204 }
6205 default:
6206 break;
6207 }
6208 } else {
6209 switch (Opcode) {
6210 case SystemZISD::SELECT_CCMASK:
6211 return computeNumSignBitsBinOp(Op, DemandedElts, DAG, Depth, 0);
6212 default:
6213 break;
6214 }
6215 }
6216
6217 return 1;
6218}
