6220//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6221// Custom insertion
6222//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6223
6224// Create a new basic block after MBB.
6225static MachineBasicBlock *emitBlockAfter(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) {
6226 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6227 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB = MF.CreateMachineBasicBlock(MBB->getBasicBlock());
6228 MF.insert(std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(MBB)), NewMBB);
6229 return NewMBB;
6230}
6231
6232// Split MBB after MI and return the new block (the one that contains
6233// instructions after MI).
6234static MachineBasicBlock *splitBlockAfter(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI,
6235 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) {
6236 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB = emitBlockAfter(MBB);
6237 NewMBB->splice(NewMBB->begin(), MBB,
6238 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), MBB->end());
6239 NewMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(MBB);
6240 return NewMBB;
6241}
6242
6243// Split MBB before MI and return the new block (the one that contains MI).
6244static MachineBasicBlock *splitBlockBefore(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI,
6245 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) {
6246 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB = emitBlockAfter(MBB);
6247 NewMBB->splice(NewMBB->begin(), MBB, MI, MBB->end());
6248 NewMBB->transferSuccessorsAndUpdatePHIs(MBB);
6249 return NewMBB;
6250}
6251
6252// Force base value Base into a register before MI. Return the register.
6253static unsigned forceReg(MachineInstr &MI, MachineOperand &Base,
6254 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII) {
6255 if (Base.isReg())
6256 return Base.getReg();
6257
6258 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent();
6259 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6260 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6261
6262 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass);
6263 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(SystemZ::LA), Reg)
6264 .add(Base)
6265 .addImm(0)
6266 .addReg(0);
6267 return Reg;
6268}
6269
6270// The CC operand of MI might be missing a kill marker because there
6271// were multiple uses of CC, and ISel didn't know which to mark.
6272// Figure out whether MI should have had a kill marker.
6273static bool checkCCKill(MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB) {
6274 // Scan forward through BB for a use/def of CC.
6275 MachineBasicBlock::iterator miI(std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)));
6276 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator miE = MBB->end(); miI != miE; ++miI) {
6277 const MachineInstr& mi = *miI;
6278 if (mi.readsRegister(SystemZ::CC))
6279 return false;
6280 if (mi.definesRegister(SystemZ::CC))
6281 break; // Should have kill-flag - update below.
6282 }
6283
6284 // If we hit the end of the block, check whether CC is live into a
6285 // successor.
6286 if (miI == MBB->end()) {
6287 for (auto SI = MBB->succ_begin(), SE = MBB->succ_end(); SI != SE; ++SI)
6288 if ((*SI)->isLiveIn(SystemZ::CC))
6289 return false;
6290 }
6291
6292 return true;
6293}
6294
6295// Return true if it is OK for this Select pseudo-opcode to be cascaded
6296// together with other Select pseudo-opcodes into a single basic-block with
6297// a conditional jump around it.
6298static bool isSelectPseudo(MachineInstr &MI) {
6299 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
6300 case SystemZ::Select32:
6301 case SystemZ::Select64:
6302 case SystemZ::SelectF32:
6303 case SystemZ::SelectF64:
6304 case SystemZ::SelectF128:
6305 case SystemZ::SelectVR32:
6306 case SystemZ::SelectVR64:
6307 case SystemZ::SelectVR128:
6308 return true;
6309
6310 default:
6311 return false;
6312 }
6313}
6314
6315// Helper function, which inserts PHI functions into SinkMBB:
6316// %Result(i) = phi [ %FalseValue(i), FalseMBB ], [ %TrueValue(i), TrueMBB ],
6317// where %FalseValue(i) and %TrueValue(i) are taken from the consequent Selects
6318// in [MIItBegin, MIItEnd) range.
6319static void createPHIsForSelects(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItBegin,
6320 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItEnd,
6321 MachineBasicBlock *TrueMBB,
6322 MachineBasicBlock *FalseMBB,
6323 MachineBasicBlock *SinkMBB) {
6324 MachineFunction *MF = TrueMBB->getParent();
6325 const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
6326
6327 unsigned CCValid = MIItBegin->getOperand(3).getImm();
6328 unsigned CCMask = MIItBegin->getOperand(4).getImm();
6329 DebugLoc DL = MIItBegin->getDebugLoc();
6330
6331 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SinkInsertionPoint = SinkMBB->begin();
6332
6333 // As we are creating the PHIs, we have to be careful if there is more than
6334 // one. Later Selects may reference the results of earlier Selects, but later
6335 // PHIs have to reference the individual true/false inputs from earlier PHIs.
6336 // That also means that PHI construction must work forward from earlier to
6337 // later, and that the code must maintain a mapping from earlier PHI's
6338 // destination registers, and the registers that went into the PHI.
6339 DenseMap<unsigned, std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>> RegRewriteTable;
6340
6341 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIIt = MIItBegin; MIIt != MIItEnd;
6342 MIIt = skipDebugInstructionsForward(++MIIt, MIItEnd)) {
6343 unsigned DestReg = MIIt->getOperand(0).getReg();
6344 unsigned TrueReg = MIIt->getOperand(1).getReg();
6345 unsigned FalseReg = MIIt->getOperand(2).getReg();
6346
6347 // If this Select we are generating is the opposite condition from
6348 // the jump we generated, then we have to swap the operands for the
6349 // PHI that is going to be generated.
6350 if (MIIt->getOperand(4).getImm() == (CCValid ^ CCMask))
6351 std::swap(TrueReg, FalseReg);
6352
6353 if (RegRewriteTable.find(TrueReg) != RegRewriteTable.end())
6354 TrueReg = RegRewriteTable[TrueReg].first;
6355
6356 if (RegRewriteTable.find(FalseReg) != RegRewriteTable.end())
6357 FalseReg = RegRewriteTable[FalseReg].second;
6358
6359 BuildMI(*SinkMBB, SinkInsertionPoint, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), DestReg)
6360 .addReg(TrueReg).addMBB(TrueMBB)
6361 .addReg(FalseReg).addMBB(FalseMBB);
6362
6363 // Add this PHI to the rewrite table.
6364 RegRewriteTable[DestReg] = std::make_pair(TrueReg, FalseReg);
6365 }
6366
6367 MF->getProperties().reset(MachineFunctionProperties::Property::NoPHIs);
6368}
6369
6370// Implement EmitInstrWithCustomInserter for pseudo Select* instruction MI.
6371MachineBasicBlock *
6372SystemZTargetLowering::emitSelect(MachineInstr &MI,
6373 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
6374 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6375 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6376
6377 unsigned CCValid = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
6378 unsigned CCMask = MI.getOperand(4).getImm();
6379 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6380
6381 // If we have a sequence of Select* pseudo instructions using the
6382 // same condition code value, we want to expand all of them into
6383 // a single pair of basic blocks using the same condition.
6384 MachineInstr *LastMI = &MI;
6385 MachineBasicBlock::iterator NextMIIt = skipDebugInstructionsForward(
6386 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)), MBB->end());
6387
6388 if (isSelectPseudo(MI))
6389 while (NextMIIt != MBB->end() && isSelectPseudo(*NextMIIt) &&
6390 NextMIIt->getOperand(3).getImm() == CCValid &&
6391 (NextMIIt->getOperand(4).getImm() == CCMask ||
6392 NextMIIt->getOperand(4).getImm() == (CCValid ^ CCMask))) {
6393 LastMI = &*NextMIIt;
6394 NextMIIt = skipDebugInstructionsForward(++NextMIIt, MBB->end());
6395 }
6396
6397 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6398 MachineBasicBlock *JoinMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6399 MachineBasicBlock *FalseMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6400
6401 // Unless CC was killed in the last Select instruction, mark it as
6402 // live-in to both FalseMBB and JoinMBB.
6403 if (!LastMI->killsRegister(SystemZ::CC) && !checkCCKill(*LastMI, JoinMBB)) {
6404 FalseMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
6405 JoinMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
6406 }
6407
6408 // StartMBB:
6409 // BRC CCMask, JoinMBB
6410 // # fallthrough to FalseMBB
6411 MBB = StartMBB;
6412 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6413 .addImm(CCValid).addImm(CCMask).addMBB(JoinMBB);
6414 MBB->addSuccessor(JoinMBB);
6415 MBB->addSuccessor(FalseMBB);
6416
6417 // FalseMBB:
6418 // # fallthrough to JoinMBB
6419 MBB = FalseMBB;
6420 MBB->addSuccessor(JoinMBB);
6421
6422 // JoinMBB:
6423 // %Result = phi [ %FalseReg, FalseMBB ], [ %TrueReg, StartMBB ]
6424 // ...
6425 MBB = JoinMBB;
6426 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItBegin = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI);
6427 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MIItEnd = skipDebugInstructionsForward(
6428 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(LastMI)), MBB->end());
6429 createPHIsForSelects(MIItBegin, MIItEnd, StartMBB, FalseMBB, MBB);
6430
6431 StartMBB->erase(MIItBegin, MIItEnd);
6432 return JoinMBB;
6433}
6434
6435// Implement EmitInstrWithCustomInserter for pseudo CondStore* instruction MI.
6436// StoreOpcode is the store to use and Invert says whether the store should
6437// happen when the condition is false rather than true. If a STORE ON
6438// CONDITION is available, STOCOpcode is its opcode, otherwise it is 0.
6439MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitCondStore(MachineInstr &MI,
6440 MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
6441 unsigned StoreOpcode,
6442 unsigned STOCOpcode,
6443 bool Invert) const {
6444 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6445 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6446
6447 unsigned SrcReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6448 MachineOperand Base = MI.getOperand(1);
6449 int64_t Disp = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
6450 unsigned IndexReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
6451 unsigned CCValid = MI.getOperand(4).getImm();
6452 unsigned CCMask = MI.getOperand(5).getImm();
6453 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6454
6455 StoreOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(StoreOpcode, Disp);
6456
6457 // Use STOCOpcode if possible. We could use different store patterns in
6458 // order to avoid matching the index register, but the performance trade-offs
6459 // might be more complicated in that case.
6460 if (STOCOpcode && !IndexReg && Subtarget.hasLoadStoreOnCond()) {
6461 if (Invert)
6462 CCMask ^= CCValid;
6463
6464 // ISel pattern matching also adds a load memory operand of the same
6465 // address, so take special care to find the storing memory operand.
6466 MachineMemOperand *MMO = nullptr;
6467 for (auto *I : MI.memoperands())
6468 if (I->isStore()) {
6469 MMO = I;
6470 break;
6471 }
6472
6473 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(STOCOpcode))
6474 .addReg(SrcReg)
6475 .add(Base)
6476 .addImm(Disp)
6477 .addImm(CCValid)
6478 .addImm(CCMask)
6479 .addMemOperand(MMO);
6480
6481 MI.eraseFromParent();
6482 return MBB;
6483 }
6484
6485 // Get the condition needed to branch around the store.
6486 if (!Invert)
6487 CCMask ^= CCValid;
6488
6489 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6490 MachineBasicBlock *JoinMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6491 MachineBasicBlock *FalseMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6492
6493 // Unless CC was killed in the CondStore instruction, mark it as
6494 // live-in to both FalseMBB and JoinMBB.
6495 if (!MI.killsRegister(SystemZ::CC) && !checkCCKill(MI, JoinMBB)) {
6496 FalseMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
6497 JoinMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
6498 }
6499
6500 // StartMBB:
6501 // BRC CCMask, JoinMBB
6502 // # fallthrough to FalseMBB
6503 MBB = StartMBB;
6504 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6505 .addImm(CCValid).addImm(CCMask).addMBB(JoinMBB);
6506 MBB->addSuccessor(JoinMBB);
6507 MBB->addSuccessor(FalseMBB);
6508
6509 // FalseMBB:
6510 // store %SrcReg, %Disp(%Index,%Base)
6511 // # fallthrough to JoinMBB
6512 MBB = FalseMBB;
6513 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(StoreOpcode))
6514 .addReg(SrcReg)
6515 .add(Base)
6516 .addImm(Disp)
6517 .addReg(IndexReg);
6518 MBB->addSuccessor(JoinMBB);
6519
6520 MI.eraseFromParent();
6521 return JoinMBB;
6522}
6523
6524// Implement EmitInstrWithCustomInserter for pseudo ATOMIC_LOAD{,W}_*
6525// or ATOMIC_SWAP{,W} instruction MI. BinOpcode is the instruction that
6526// performs the binary operation elided by "*", or 0 for ATOMIC_SWAP{,W}.
6527// BitSize is the width of the field in bits, or 0 if this is a partword
6528// ATOMIC_LOADW_* or ATOMIC_SWAPW instruction, in which case the bitsize
6529// is one of the operands. Invert says whether the field should be
6530// inverted after performing BinOpcode (e.g. for NAND).
6531MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitAtomicLoadBinary(
6532 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned BinOpcode,
6533 unsigned BitSize, bool Invert) const {
6534 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6535 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6536 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6537 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6538 bool IsSubWord = (BitSize < 32);
6539
6540 // Extract the operands. Base can be a register or a frame index.
6541 // Src2 can be a register or immediate.
6542 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6543 MachineOperand Base = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(1));
6544 int64_t Disp = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
6545 MachineOperand Src2 = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(3));
6546 unsigned BitShift = (IsSubWord ? MI.getOperand(4).getReg() : 0);
6547 unsigned NegBitShift = (IsSubWord ? MI.getOperand(5).getReg() : 0);
6548 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6549 if (IsSubWord)
6550 BitSize = MI.getOperand(6).getImm();
6551
6552 // Subword operations use 32-bit registers.
6553 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = (BitSize <= 32 ?
6554 &SystemZ::GR32BitRegClass :
6555 &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass);
6556 unsigned LOpcode = BitSize <= 32 ? SystemZ::L : SystemZ::LG;
6557 unsigned CSOpcode = BitSize <= 32 ? SystemZ::CS : SystemZ::CSG;
6558
6559 // Get the right opcodes for the displacement.
6560 LOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(LOpcode, Disp);
6561 CSOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(CSOpcode, Disp);
6562 assert(LOpcode && CSOpcode && "Displacement out of range");
6563
6564 // Create virtual registers for temporary results.
6565 unsigned OrigVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6566 unsigned OldVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6567 unsigned NewVal = (BinOpcode || IsSubWord ?
6568 MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : Src2.getReg());
6569 unsigned RotatedOldVal = (IsSubWord ? MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : OldVal);
6570 unsigned RotatedNewVal = (IsSubWord ? MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : NewVal);
6571
6572 // Insert a basic block for the main loop.
6573 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6574 MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6575 MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6576
6577 // StartMBB:
6578 // ...
6579 // %OrigVal = L Disp(%Base)
6580 // # fall through to LoopMMB
6581 MBB = StartMBB;
6582 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(LOpcode), OrigVal).add(Base).addImm(Disp).addReg(0);
6583 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6584
6585 // LoopMBB:
6586 // %OldVal = phi [ %OrigVal, StartMBB ], [ %Dest, LoopMBB ]
6587 // %RotatedOldVal = RLL %OldVal, 0(%BitShift)
6588 // %RotatedNewVal = OP %RotatedOldVal, %Src2
6589 // %NewVal = RLL %RotatedNewVal, 0(%NegBitShift)
6590 // %Dest = CS %OldVal, %NewVal, Disp(%Base)
6591 // JNE LoopMBB
6592 // # fall through to DoneMMB
6593 MBB = LoopMBB;
6594 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), OldVal)
6595 .addReg(OrigVal).addMBB(StartMBB)
6596 .addReg(Dest).addMBB(LoopMBB);
6597 if (IsSubWord)
6598 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), RotatedOldVal)
6599 .addReg(OldVal).addReg(BitShift).addImm(0);
6600 if (Invert) {
6601 // Perform the operation normally and then invert every bit of the field.
6602 unsigned Tmp = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6603 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(BinOpcode), Tmp).addReg(RotatedOldVal).add(Src2);
6604 if (BitSize <= 32)
6605 // XILF with the upper BitSize bits set.
6606 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::XILF), RotatedNewVal)
6607 .addReg(Tmp).addImm(-1U << (32 - BitSize));
6608 else {
6609 // Use LCGR and add -1 to the result, which is more compact than
6610 // an XILF, XILH pair.
6611 unsigned Tmp2 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6612 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LCGR), Tmp2).addReg(Tmp);
6613 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::AGHI), RotatedNewVal)
6614 .addReg(Tmp2).addImm(-1);
6615 }
6616 } else if (BinOpcode)
6617 // A simply binary operation.
6618 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(BinOpcode), RotatedNewVal)
6619 .addReg(RotatedOldVal)
6620 .add(Src2);
6621 else if (IsSubWord)
6622 // Use RISBG to rotate Src2 into position and use it to replace the
6623 // field in RotatedOldVal.
6624 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RISBG32), RotatedNewVal)
6625 .addReg(RotatedOldVal).addReg(Src2.getReg())
6626 .addImm(32).addImm(31 + BitSize).addImm(32 - BitSize);
6627 if (IsSubWord)
6628 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), NewVal)
6629 .addReg(RotatedNewVal).addReg(NegBitShift).addImm(0);
6630 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(CSOpcode), Dest)
6631 .addReg(OldVal)
6632 .addReg(NewVal)
6633 .add(Base)
6634 .addImm(Disp);
6635 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6636 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS_NE).addMBB(LoopMBB);
6637 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6638 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
6639
6640 MI.eraseFromParent();
6641 return DoneMBB;
6642}
6643
6644// Implement EmitInstrWithCustomInserter for pseudo
6645// ATOMIC_LOAD{,W}_{,U}{MIN,MAX} instruction MI. CompareOpcode is the
6646// instruction that should be used to compare the current field with the
6647// minimum or maximum value. KeepOldMask is the BRC condition-code mask
6648// for when the current field should be kept. BitSize is the width of
6649// the field in bits, or 0 if this is a partword ATOMIC_LOADW_* instruction.
6650MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitAtomicLoadMinMax(
6651 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned CompareOpcode,
6652 unsigned KeepOldMask, unsigned BitSize) const {
6653 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6654 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6655 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6656 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6657 bool IsSubWord = (BitSize < 32);
6658
6659 // Extract the operands. Base can be a register or a frame index.
6660 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6661 MachineOperand Base = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(1));
6662 int64_t Disp = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
6663 unsigned Src2 = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
6664 unsigned BitShift = (IsSubWord ? MI.getOperand(4).getReg() : 0);
6665 unsigned NegBitShift = (IsSubWord ? MI.getOperand(5).getReg() : 0);
6666 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6667 if (IsSubWord)
6668 BitSize = MI.getOperand(6).getImm();
6669
6670 // Subword operations use 32-bit registers.
6671 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = (BitSize <= 32 ?
6672 &SystemZ::GR32BitRegClass :
6673 &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass);
6674 unsigned LOpcode = BitSize <= 32 ? SystemZ::L : SystemZ::LG;
6675 unsigned CSOpcode = BitSize <= 32 ? SystemZ::CS : SystemZ::CSG;
6676
6677 // Get the right opcodes for the displacement.
6678 LOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(LOpcode, Disp);
6679 CSOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(CSOpcode, Disp);
6680 assert(LOpcode && CSOpcode && "Displacement out of range");
6681
6682 // Create virtual registers for temporary results.
6683 unsigned OrigVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6684 unsigned OldVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6685 unsigned NewVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6686 unsigned RotatedOldVal = (IsSubWord ? MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : OldVal);
6687 unsigned RotatedAltVal = (IsSubWord ? MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : Src2);
6688 unsigned RotatedNewVal = (IsSubWord ? MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC) : NewVal);
6689
6690 // Insert 3 basic blocks for the loop.
6691 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6692 MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6693 MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6694 MachineBasicBlock *UseAltMBB = emitBlockAfter(LoopMBB);
6695 MachineBasicBlock *UpdateMBB = emitBlockAfter(UseAltMBB);
6696
6697 // StartMBB:
6698 // ...
6699 // %OrigVal = L Disp(%Base)
6700 // # fall through to LoopMMB
6701 MBB = StartMBB;
6702 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(LOpcode), OrigVal).add(Base).addImm(Disp).addReg(0);
6703 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6704
6705 // LoopMBB:
6706 // %OldVal = phi [ %OrigVal, StartMBB ], [ %Dest, UpdateMBB ]
6707 // %RotatedOldVal = RLL %OldVal, 0(%BitShift)
6708 // CompareOpcode %RotatedOldVal, %Src2
6709 // BRC KeepOldMask, UpdateMBB
6710 MBB = LoopMBB;
6711 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), OldVal)
6712 .addReg(OrigVal).addMBB(StartMBB)
6713 .addReg(Dest).addMBB(UpdateMBB);
6714 if (IsSubWord)
6715 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), RotatedOldVal)
6716 .addReg(OldVal).addReg(BitShift).addImm(0);
6717 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(CompareOpcode))
6718 .addReg(RotatedOldVal).addReg(Src2);
6719 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6720 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(KeepOldMask).addMBB(UpdateMBB);
6721 MBB->addSuccessor(UpdateMBB);
6722 MBB->addSuccessor(UseAltMBB);
6723
6724 // UseAltMBB:
6725 // %RotatedAltVal = RISBG %RotatedOldVal, %Src2, 32, 31 + BitSize, 0
6726 // # fall through to UpdateMMB
6727 MBB = UseAltMBB;
6728 if (IsSubWord)
6729 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RISBG32), RotatedAltVal)
6730 .addReg(RotatedOldVal).addReg(Src2)
6731 .addImm(32).addImm(31 + BitSize).addImm(0);
6732 MBB->addSuccessor(UpdateMBB);
6733
6734 // UpdateMBB:
6735 // %RotatedNewVal = PHI [ %RotatedOldVal, LoopMBB ],
6736 // [ %RotatedAltVal, UseAltMBB ]
6737 // %NewVal = RLL %RotatedNewVal, 0(%NegBitShift)
6738 // %Dest = CS %OldVal, %NewVal, Disp(%Base)
6739 // JNE LoopMBB
6740 // # fall through to DoneMMB
6741 MBB = UpdateMBB;
6742 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), RotatedNewVal)
6743 .addReg(RotatedOldVal).addMBB(LoopMBB)
6744 .addReg(RotatedAltVal).addMBB(UseAltMBB);
6745 if (IsSubWord)
6746 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), NewVal)
6747 .addReg(RotatedNewVal).addReg(NegBitShift).addImm(0);
6748 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(CSOpcode), Dest)
6749 .addReg(OldVal)
6750 .addReg(NewVal)
6751 .add(Base)
6752 .addImm(Disp);
6753 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6754 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS_NE).addMBB(LoopMBB);
6755 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6756 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
6757
6758 MI.eraseFromParent();
6759 return DoneMBB;
6760}
6761
6762// Implement EmitInstrWithCustomInserter for pseudo ATOMIC_CMP_SWAPW
6763// instruction MI.
6764MachineBasicBlock *
6765SystemZTargetLowering::emitAtomicCmpSwapW(MachineInstr &MI,
6766 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
6767
6768 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6769 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6770 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6771 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6772
6773 // Extract the operands. Base can be a register or a frame index.
6774 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6775 MachineOperand Base = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(1));
6776 int64_t Disp = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
6777 unsigned OrigCmpVal = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
6778 unsigned OrigSwapVal = MI.getOperand(4).getReg();
6779 unsigned BitShift = MI.getOperand(5).getReg();
6780 unsigned NegBitShift = MI.getOperand(6).getReg();
6781 int64_t BitSize = MI.getOperand(7).getImm();
6782 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6783
6784 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &SystemZ::GR32BitRegClass;
6785
6786 // Get the right opcodes for the displacement.
6787 unsigned LOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(SystemZ::L, Disp);
6788 unsigned CSOpcode = TII->getOpcodeForOffset(SystemZ::CS, Disp);
6789 assert(LOpcode && CSOpcode && "Displacement out of range");
6790
6791 // Create virtual registers for temporary results.
6792 unsigned OrigOldVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6793 unsigned OldVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6794 unsigned CmpVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6795 unsigned SwapVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6796 unsigned StoreVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6797 unsigned RetryOldVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6798 unsigned RetryCmpVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6799 unsigned RetrySwapVal = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6800
6801 // Insert 2 basic blocks for the loop.
6802 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6803 MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6804 MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6805 MachineBasicBlock *SetMBB = emitBlockAfter(LoopMBB);
6806
6807 // StartMBB:
6808 // ...
6809 // %OrigOldVal = L Disp(%Base)
6810 // # fall through to LoopMMB
6811 MBB = StartMBB;
6812 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(LOpcode), OrigOldVal)
6813 .add(Base)
6814 .addImm(Disp)
6815 .addReg(0);
6816 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6817
6818 // LoopMBB:
6819 // %OldVal = phi [ %OrigOldVal, EntryBB ], [ %RetryOldVal, SetMBB ]
6820 // %CmpVal = phi [ %OrigCmpVal, EntryBB ], [ %RetryCmpVal, SetMBB ]
6821 // %SwapVal = phi [ %OrigSwapVal, EntryBB ], [ %RetrySwapVal, SetMBB ]
6822 // %Dest = RLL %OldVal, BitSize(%BitShift)
6823 // ^^ The low BitSize bits contain the field
6824 // of interest.
6825 // %RetryCmpVal = RISBG32 %CmpVal, %Dest, 32, 63-BitSize, 0
6826 // ^^ Replace the upper 32-BitSize bits of the
6827 // comparison value with those that we loaded,
6828 // so that we can use a full word comparison.
6829 // CR %Dest, %RetryCmpVal
6830 // JNE DoneMBB
6831 // # Fall through to SetMBB
6832 MBB = LoopMBB;
6833 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), OldVal)
6834 .addReg(OrigOldVal).addMBB(StartMBB)
6835 .addReg(RetryOldVal).addMBB(SetMBB);
6836 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), CmpVal)
6837 .addReg(OrigCmpVal).addMBB(StartMBB)
6838 .addReg(RetryCmpVal).addMBB(SetMBB);
6839 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), SwapVal)
6840 .addReg(OrigSwapVal).addMBB(StartMBB)
6841 .addReg(RetrySwapVal).addMBB(SetMBB);
6842 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), Dest)
6843 .addReg(OldVal).addReg(BitShift).addImm(BitSize);
6844 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RISBG32), RetryCmpVal)
6845 .addReg(CmpVal).addReg(Dest).addImm(32).addImm(63 - BitSize).addImm(0);
6846 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::CR))
6847 .addReg(Dest).addReg(RetryCmpVal);
6848 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6849 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP)
6850 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE).addMBB(DoneMBB);
6851 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
6852 MBB->addSuccessor(SetMBB);
6853
6854 // SetMBB:
6855 // %RetrySwapVal = RISBG32 %SwapVal, %Dest, 32, 63-BitSize, 0
6856 // ^^ Replace the upper 32-BitSize bits of the new
6857 // value with those that we loaded.
6858 // %StoreVal = RLL %RetrySwapVal, -BitSize(%NegBitShift)
6859 // ^^ Rotate the new field to its proper position.
6860 // %RetryOldVal = CS %Dest, %StoreVal, Disp(%Base)
6861 // JNE LoopMBB
6862 // # fall through to ExitMMB
6863 MBB = SetMBB;
6864 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RISBG32), RetrySwapVal)
6865 .addReg(SwapVal).addReg(Dest).addImm(32).addImm(63 - BitSize).addImm(0);
6866 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::RLL), StoreVal)
6867 .addReg(RetrySwapVal).addReg(NegBitShift).addImm(-BitSize);
6868 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(CSOpcode), RetryOldVal)
6869 .addReg(OldVal)
6870 .addReg(StoreVal)
6871 .add(Base)
6872 .addImm(Disp);
6873 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
6874 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CS_NE).addMBB(LoopMBB);
6875 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6876 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
6877
6878 // If the CC def wasn't dead in the ATOMIC_CMP_SWAPW, mark CC as live-in
6879 // to the block after the loop. At this point, CC may have been defined
6880 // either by the CR in LoopMBB or by the CS in SetMBB.
6881 if (!MI.registerDefIsDead(SystemZ::CC))
6882 DoneMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
6883
6884 MI.eraseFromParent();
6885 return DoneMBB;
6886}
6887
6888// Emit a move from two GR64s to a GR128.
6889MachineBasicBlock *
6890SystemZTargetLowering::emitPair128(MachineInstr &MI,
6891 MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
6892 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6893 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6894 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6895 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6896 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6897
6898 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6899 unsigned Hi = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
6900 unsigned Lo = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
6901 unsigned Tmp1 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
6902 unsigned Tmp2 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
6903
6904 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), Tmp1);
6905 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), Tmp2)
6906 .addReg(Tmp1).addReg(Hi).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_h64);
6907 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), Dest)
6908 .addReg(Tmp2).addReg(Lo).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_l64);
6909
6910 MI.eraseFromParent();
6911 return MBB;
6912}
6913
6914// Emit an extension from a GR64 to a GR128. ClearEven is true
6915// if the high register of the GR128 value must be cleared or false if
6916// it's "don't care".
6917MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitExt128(MachineInstr &MI,
6918 MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
6919 bool ClearEven) const {
6920 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6921 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6922 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6923 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6924 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6925
6926 unsigned Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
6927 unsigned Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
6928 unsigned In128 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
6929
6930 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), In128);
6931 if (ClearEven) {
6932 unsigned NewIn128 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
6933 unsigned Zero64 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass);
6934
6935 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LLILL), Zero64)
6936 .addImm(0);
6937 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), NewIn128)
6938 .addReg(In128).addReg(Zero64).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_h64);
6939 In128 = NewIn128;
6940 }
6941 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), Dest)
6942 .addReg(In128).addReg(Src).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_l64);
6943
6944 MI.eraseFromParent();
6945 return MBB;
6946}
6947
6948MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitMemMemWrapper(
6949 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
6950 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
6951 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
6952 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
6953 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
6954 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
6955
6956 MachineOperand DestBase = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(0));
6957 uint64_t DestDisp = MI.getOperand(1).getImm();
6958 MachineOperand SrcBase = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(2));
6959 uint64_t SrcDisp = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
6960 uint64_t Length = MI.getOperand(4).getImm();
6961
6962 // When generating more than one CLC, all but the last will need to
6963 // branch to the end when a difference is found.
6964 MachineBasicBlock *EndMBB = (Length > 256 && Opcode == SystemZ::CLC ?
6965 splitBlockAfter(MI, MBB) : nullptr);
6966
6967 // Check for the loop form, in which operand 5 is the trip count.
6968 if (MI.getNumExplicitOperands() > 5) {
6969 bool HaveSingleBase = DestBase.isIdenticalTo(SrcBase);
6970
6971 uint64_t StartCountReg = MI.getOperand(5).getReg();
6972 uint64_t StartSrcReg = forceReg(MI, SrcBase, TII);
6973 uint64_t StartDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? StartSrcReg :
6974 forceReg(MI, DestBase, TII));
6975
6976 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass;
6977 uint64_t ThisSrcReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6978 uint64_t ThisDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? ThisSrcReg :
6979 MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC));
6980 uint64_t NextSrcReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6981 uint64_t NextDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? NextSrcReg :
6982 MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC));
6983
6984 RC = &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass;
6985 uint64_t ThisCountReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6986 uint64_t NextCountReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
6987
6988 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
6989 MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
6990 MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
6991 MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB = (EndMBB ? emitBlockAfter(LoopMBB) : LoopMBB);
6992
6993 // StartMBB:
6994 // # fall through to LoopMMB
6995 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
6996
6997 // LoopMBB:
6998 // %ThisDestReg = phi [ %StartDestReg, StartMBB ],
6999 // [ %NextDestReg, NextMBB ]
7000 // %ThisSrcReg = phi [ %StartSrcReg, StartMBB ],
7001 // [ %NextSrcReg, NextMBB ]
7002 // %ThisCountReg = phi [ %StartCountReg, StartMBB ],
7003 // [ %NextCountReg, NextMBB ]
7004 // ( PFD 2, 768+DestDisp(%ThisDestReg) )
7005 // Opcode DestDisp(256,%ThisDestReg), SrcDisp(%ThisSrcReg)
7006 // ( JLH EndMBB )
7007 //
7008 // The prefetch is used only for MVC. The JLH is used only for CLC.
7009 MBB = LoopMBB;
7010
7011 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisDestReg)
7012 .addReg(StartDestReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7013 .addReg(NextDestReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7014 if (!HaveSingleBase)
7015 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisSrcReg)
7016 .addReg(StartSrcReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7017 .addReg(NextSrcReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7018 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisCountReg)
7019 .addReg(StartCountReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7020 .addReg(NextCountReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7021 if (Opcode == SystemZ::MVC)
7022 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PFD))
7023 .addImm(SystemZ::PFD_WRITE)
7024 .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(DestDisp + 768).addReg(0);
7025 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7026 .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(DestDisp).addImm(256)
7027 .addReg(ThisSrcReg).addImm(SrcDisp);
7028 if (EndMBB) {
7029 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7030 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7031 .addMBB(EndMBB);
7032 MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7033 MBB->addSuccessor(NextMBB);
7034 }
7035
7036 // NextMBB:
7037 // %NextDestReg = LA 256(%ThisDestReg)
7038 // %NextSrcReg = LA 256(%ThisSrcReg)
7039 // %NextCountReg = AGHI %ThisCountReg, -1
7040 // CGHI %NextCountReg, 0
7041 // JLH LoopMBB
7042 // # fall through to DoneMMB
7043 //
7044 // The AGHI, CGHI and JLH should be converted to BRCTG by later passes.
7045 MBB = NextMBB;
7046
7047 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LA), NextDestReg)
7048 .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(256).addReg(0);
7049 if (!HaveSingleBase)
7050 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LA), NextSrcReg)
7051 .addReg(ThisSrcReg).addImm(256).addReg(0);
7052 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::AGHI), NextCountReg)
7053 .addReg(ThisCountReg).addImm(-1);
7054 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::CGHI))
7055 .addReg(NextCountReg).addImm(0);
7056 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7057 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7058 .addMBB(LoopMBB);
7059 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7060 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
7061
7062 DestBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(NextDestReg, false);
7063 SrcBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(NextSrcReg, false);
7064 Length &= 255;
7065 if (EndMBB && !Length)
7066 // If the loop handled the whole CLC range, DoneMBB will be empty with
7067 // CC live-through into EndMBB, so add it as live-in.
7068 DoneMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7069 MBB = DoneMBB;
7070 }
7071 // Handle any remaining bytes with straight-line code.
7072 while (Length > 0) {
7073 uint64_t ThisLength = std::min(Length, uint64_t(256));
7074 // The previous iteration might have created out-of-range displacements.
7075 // Apply them using LAY if so.
7076 if (!isUInt<12>(DestDisp)) {
7077 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass);
7078 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(SystemZ::LAY), Reg)
7079 .add(DestBase)
7080 .addImm(DestDisp)
7081 .addReg(0);
7082 DestBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false);
7083 DestDisp = 0;
7084 }
7085 if (!isUInt<12>(SrcDisp)) {
7086 unsigned Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass);
7087 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(SystemZ::LAY), Reg)
7088 .add(SrcBase)
7089 .addImm(SrcDisp)
7090 .addReg(0);
7091 SrcBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false);
7092 SrcDisp = 0;
7093 }
7094 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7095 .add(DestBase)
7096 .addImm(DestDisp)
7097 .addImm(ThisLength)
7098 .add(SrcBase)
7099 .addImm(SrcDisp)
7100 .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands());
7101 DestDisp += ThisLength;
7102 SrcDisp += ThisLength;
7103 Length -= ThisLength;
7104 // If there's another CLC to go, branch to the end if a difference
7105 // was found.
7106 if (EndMBB && Length > 0) {
7107 MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
7108 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7109 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7110 .addMBB(EndMBB);
7111 MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7112 MBB->addSuccessor(NextMBB);
7113 MBB = NextMBB;
7114 }
7115 }
7116 if (EndMBB) {
7117 MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7118 MBB = EndMBB;
7119 MBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7120 }
7121
7122 MI.eraseFromParent();
7123 return MBB;
7124}
7125
7126// Decompose string pseudo-instruction MI into a loop that continually performs
7127// Opcode until CC != 3.
7128MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitStringWrapper(
7129 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
7130 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7131 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7132 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7133 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
7134 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7135
7136 uint64_t End1Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
7137 uint64_t Start1Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
7138 uint64_t Start2Reg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
7139 uint64_t CharReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
7140
7141 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass;
7142 uint64_t This1Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7143 uint64_t This2Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7144 uint64_t End2Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7145
7146 MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
7147 MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
7148 MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
7149
7150 // StartMBB:
7151 // # fall through to LoopMMB
7152 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7153
7154 // LoopMBB:
7155 // %This1Reg = phi [ %Start1Reg, StartMBB ], [ %End1Reg, LoopMBB ]
7156 // %This2Reg = phi [ %Start2Reg, StartMBB ], [ %End2Reg, LoopMBB ]
7157 // R0L = %CharReg
7158 // %End1Reg, %End2Reg = CLST %This1Reg, %This2Reg -- uses R0L
7159 // JO LoopMBB
7160 // # fall through to DoneMMB
7161 //
7162 // The load of R0L can be hoisted by post-RA LICM.
7163 MBB = LoopMBB;
7164
7165 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), This1Reg)
7166 .addReg(Start1Reg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7167 .addReg(End1Reg).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7168 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), This2Reg)
7169 .addReg(Start2Reg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7170 .addReg(End2Reg).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7171 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), SystemZ::R0L).addReg(CharReg);
7172 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7173 .addReg(End1Reg, RegState::Define).addReg(End2Reg, RegState::Define)
7174 .addReg(This1Reg).addReg(This2Reg);
7175 BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7176 .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ANY).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_3).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7177 MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7178 MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
7179
7180 DoneMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7181
7182 MI.eraseFromParent();
7183 return DoneMBB;
7184}
7185
7186// Update TBEGIN instruction with final opcode and register clobbers.
7187MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitTransactionBegin(
7188 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode,
7189 bool NoFloat) const {
7190 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7191 const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
7192 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
7193
7194 // Update opcode.
7195 MI.setDesc(TII->get(Opcode));
7196
7197 // We cannot handle a TBEGIN that clobbers the stack or frame pointer.
7198 // Make sure to add the corresponding GRSM bits if they are missing.
7199 uint64_t Control = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
7200 static const unsigned GPRControlBit[16] = {
7201 0x8000, 0x8000, 0x4000, 0x4000, 0x2000, 0x2000, 0x1000, 0x1000,
7202 0x0800, 0x0800, 0x0400, 0x0400, 0x0200, 0x0200, 0x0100, 0x0100
7203 };
7204 Control |= GPRControlBit[15];
7205 if (TFI->hasFP(MF))
7206 Control |= GPRControlBit[11];
7207 MI.getOperand(2).setImm(Control);
7208
7209 // Add GPR clobbers.
7210 for (int I = 0; I < 16; I++) {
7211 if ((Control & GPRControlBit[I]) == 0) {
7212 unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::GR64Regs[I];
7213 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7214 }
7215 }
7216
7217 // Add FPR/VR clobbers.
7218 if (!NoFloat && (Control & 4) != 0) {
7219 if (Subtarget.hasVector()) {
7220 for (int I = 0; I < 32; I++) {
7221 unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::VR128Regs[I];
7222 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7223 }
7224 } else {
7225 for (int I = 0; I < 16; I++) {
7226 unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::FP64Regs[I];
7227 MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7228 }
7229 }
7230 }
7231
7232 return MBB;
7233}
7234
7235MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitLoadAndTestCmp0(
7236 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
7237 MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7238 MachineRegisterInfo *MRI = &MF.getRegInfo();
7239 const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7240 static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7241 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7242
7243 unsigned SrcReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
7244
7245 // Create new virtual register of the same class as source.
7246 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(SrcReg);
7247 unsigned DstReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC);
7248
7249 // Replace pseudo with a normal load-and-test that models the def as
7250 // well.
7251 BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode), DstReg)
7252 .addReg(SrcReg);
7253 MI.eraseFromParent();
7254
7255 return MBB;
7256}
7257
7258MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(
7259 MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
7260 switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
7261 case SystemZ::Select32:
7262 case SystemZ::Select64:
7263 case SystemZ::SelectF32:
7264 case SystemZ::SelectF64:
7265 case SystemZ::SelectF128:
7266 case SystemZ::SelectVR32:
7267 case SystemZ::SelectVR64:
7268 case SystemZ::SelectVR128:
7269 return emitSelect(MI, MBB);
7270
7271 case SystemZ::CondStore8Mux:
7272 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STCMux, 0, false);
7273 case SystemZ::CondStore8MuxInv:
7274 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STCMux, 0, true);
7275 case SystemZ::CondStore16Mux:
7276 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STHMux, 0, false);
7277 case SystemZ::CondStore16MuxInv:
7278 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STHMux, 0, true);
7279 case SystemZ::CondStore32Mux:
7280 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STMux, SystemZ::STOCMux, false);
7281 case SystemZ::CondStore32MuxInv:
7282 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STMux, SystemZ::STOCMux, true);
7283 case SystemZ::CondStore8:
7284 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STC, 0, false);
7285 case SystemZ::CondStore8Inv:
7286 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STC, 0, true);
7287 case SystemZ::CondStore16:
7288 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STH, 0, false);
7289 case SystemZ::CondStore16Inv:
7290 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STH, 0, true);
7291 case SystemZ::CondStore32:
7292 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::ST, SystemZ::STOC, false);
7293 case SystemZ::CondStore32Inv:
7294 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::ST, SystemZ::STOC, true);
7295 case SystemZ::CondStore64:
7296 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STG, SystemZ::STOCG, false);
7297 case SystemZ::CondStore64Inv:
7298 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STG, SystemZ::STOCG, true);
7299 case SystemZ::CondStoreF32:
7300 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STE, 0, false);
7301 case SystemZ::CondStoreF32Inv:
7302 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STE, 0, true);
7303 case SystemZ::CondStoreF64:
7304 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STD, 0, false);
7305 case SystemZ::CondStoreF64Inv:
7306 return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STD, 0, true);
7307
7308 case SystemZ::PAIR128:
7309 return emitPair128(MI, MBB);
7310 case SystemZ::AEXT128:
7311 return emitExt128(MI, MBB, false);
7312 case SystemZ::ZEXT128:
7313 return emitExt128(MI, MBB, true);
7314
7315 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAPW:
7316 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 0);
7317 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAP_32:
7318 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 32);
7319 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAP_64:
7320 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 64);
7321
7322 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_AR:
7323 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AR, 0);
7324 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_AFI:
7325 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AFI, 0);
7326 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AR:
7327 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AR, 32);
7328 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AHI:
7329 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AHI, 32);
7330 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AFI:
7331 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AFI, 32);
7332 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGR:
7333 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGR, 64);
7334 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGHI:
7335 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGHI, 64);
7336 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGFI:
7337 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGFI, 64);
7338
7339 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_SR:
7340 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SR, 0);
7341 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_SR:
7342 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SR, 32);
7343 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_SGR:
7344 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SGR, 64);
7345
7346 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_NR:
7347 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NR, 0);
7348 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_NILH:
7349 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NILH, 0);
7350 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_NR:
7351 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NR, 32);
7352 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_NILL:
7353 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NILL, 32);
7354 case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_NILH:
7355 return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NILH, 32);

7500 return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::CLST);
7501 case SystemZ::MVSTLoop:
7502 return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::MVST);
7503 case SystemZ::SRSTLoop:
7504 return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SRST);
7505 case SystemZ::TBEGIN:
7506 return emitTransactionBegin(MI, MBB, SystemZ::TBEGIN, false);
7507 case SystemZ::TBEGIN_nofloat:
7508 return emitTransactionBegin(MI, MBB, SystemZ::TBEGIN, true);
7509 case SystemZ::TBEGINC:

7513 case SystemZ::LTDBRCompare_VecPseudo:
7514 return emitLoadAndTestCmp0(MI, MBB, SystemZ::LTDBR);

7518 case TargetOpcode::STACKMAP:
7519 case TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT:
7520 return emitPatchPoint(MI, MBB);
7521
7522 default:
7523 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instr type to insert");
7524 }

7526
7527// This is only used by the isel schedulers, and is needed only to prevent
7528// compiler from crashing when list-ilp is used.
7529const TargetRegisterClass *
7530SystemZTargetLowering::getRepRegClassFor(MVT VT) const {
7531 if (VT == MVT::Untyped)
7532 return &SystemZ::ADDR128BitRegClass;
7533 return TargetLowering::getRepRegClassFor(VT);
7534}
